{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Extend requirements for annual MOT tests to trailers including trailer caravans",
        "additional_details": "There are frequent delays on roadways caused by faulty trailers including trailer caravans. Vehicles are tested annually but towed vehicles and trailers do not have to be tested, meaning a faulty unit is less likely to be identified prior to an accident. A certificated of roadworthiness test would help an owner know a trailer or trailer caravan was safe to be on the road",
        "background": "An annual quality inspection should raise awareness and safety standards of all towed vehicles on the roads and help reduce road traffic incidents caused by faulty units.",
